    <section id="overview">
      <h2>Year Overview</h2>
      <p>The Ox (<span class="chinese-char">牛</span>) occupies the Earthly Branch <strong>Chou (丑)</strong>, carrying Earth energy with hidden Water and Metal. In the 2026 Fire Horse year, the Ox benefits from the <strong>generating cycle</strong> — Fire produces Earth, meaning the year's dominant energy nourishes the Ox's core nature.</p>
      <p>Unlike the dramatic clashes experienced by the Rat or Horse, the Ox's 2026 is characterised by <strong>gradual, solid progress</strong>. The Ox-Horse relationship carries a subtle tension — the Ox's methodical Earth nature can feel overwhelmed by Fire's urgency — but this friction is manageable and even productive. The year asks the Ox to move slightly faster than comfortable, which builds capacity.</p>
      <p>The Bing (丙) Heavenly Stem illuminates the Ox's hidden strengths, bringing recognition for work that may have gone unnoticed in previous years. Authority figures and institutional structures are supportive. This is an excellent year for the Ox to consolidate gains and build foundations for the next several years.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="career">
      <h2>Career &amp; Finance</h2>
      <p>The Fire-Earth dynamic creates <strong>productive energy for career growth</strong>. Promotions, expanded responsibilities, and recognition from superiors are favoured. The Ox's reputation for reliability becomes especially valuable in a volatile Fire Horse year — when others are swept up in impulsive decisions, the Ox's steady hand stands out.</p>
      <p><strong>Finance</strong> benefits from the Earth element's supportive energy. Property investments, long-term savings plans, and established business ventures perform well. The Ox should resist the temptation to follow others into speculative or fast-moving investments that suit Fire signs but not Earth temperaments.</p>
      <p><strong>Best sectors:</strong> Real estate, agriculture, mining, manufacturing, education, and government — all Earth-aligned industries that benefit from Fire's generating energy.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="love">
      <h2>Love &amp; Relationships</h2>
      <p>The Ox's love life in 2026 is <strong>warm but not dramatic</strong>. Fire's energy adds passion and expressiveness to the normally reserved Ox, making this a good year for deepening existing relationships. Partners appreciate the Ox's increased willingness to communicate feelings and plan shared experiences.</p>
      <p><strong>Single Oxen</strong> may find romantic prospects through professional channels — work colleagues, industry events, or educational settings. The connection between Fire (visibility) and Earth (stability) means the Ox attracts partners who value substance over flash. April (Dragon month, Ox's ally) and October (Dog month) are particularly favourable for new connections.</p>
      <p><strong>Family relationships</strong> are harmonious, with the Ox taking on a supportive, guiding role. The Rat (Ox's secret friend) benefits from the Ox's stabilising influence during the Rat's clash year.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="health">
      <h2>Health &amp; Wellness</h2>
      <p>Fire generating Earth can lead to <strong>excess Earth energy</strong>, which manifests in Chinese medicine as digestive sluggishness, weight gain, or overthinking. The Ox should focus on maintaining an active lifestyle — the tendency toward sedentary habits is amplified this year.</p>
      <p><strong>Spleen and stomach health</strong> require attention. Light, easily digestible foods are preferable to heavy, rich meals. Regular meal times and mindful eating habits support the Earth organs that are most affected.</p>
      <p><strong>Exercise</strong> should emphasise movement and circulation — walking, gentle martial arts, or yoga help counteract Earth's heaviness. The Ox benefits from outdoor activity, particularly in natural settings with good air circulation.</p>
    </section>

